title: American Veterans with Brain Injuries (AVBI)

title: Answers for Veteran or Active Military with Paralysis or Brain Injury
content: Learn about resources available from the Christopher and Dana Reeve Foundation Paralysis Resource Center, the Defense and Veterans Brain Injury Center and the Brain Injury Association of America to enhance the care of people with paralysis and traumatic brain injury.

title: Army Behavioral Health
content: Learn about post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), traumatic brain injury (TBI) and suicide prevention. Includes help for children, couples and extended families.

title: Basic Facts about TBI Video
content: Watch a video from the Brain and Spinal Cord Injury Center provides a basic overview of TBI.

title: Betty Clooney Foundation for Persons with Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)
content: Provides resources in finding the right treatment, therapy and rehabilitation for patients with TBI. Includes information on Soldiers & TBI, services available at their facility in Southern California and a listing of Support Groups in California.

title: Blast Injury FAQs
content: Offers answers to frequently asked questions about blast injuries provided by the Defense & Veterans Brain Injury Center (DVBIC).

title: Bob Woodruff Foundation
content: Provides resources and support to injured Service Members, Veterans and their families, especially those who have sustained the hidden injuries of war.

title: Brain Injury Network
content: Provides advocacy, peer support, and resources for survivors of acquired brain injury (ABI), which includes traumatic brain injury (TBI), stroke, brain illness and brain tumors.

title: BrainLine
content: Provides a variety of information and resources on traumatic brain injury (TBI).

title: Defense Centers of Excellence (DCoE)
content: Access a DoD program that works to improve psychological health and TBI treatment of Service Members and Veterans.

title: Employment after Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)

title: Facts About Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)
content: Learn about TBI from the Brain Injury Association of America (BIAA). BIAA also offers an online directory of brain injury rehabilitation programs and services across the US.

title: Healthcare for Headaches
content: Provides educational and informational resources supporting headache research and treatment. The website provide articles that link headaches to TBI and PTSD.

title: Improved Treatment for Stuttering
content: Provides free online resources, services and support to those who stutter and their families, as well as support for research into the causes of stuttering.

title: Mild Traumatic Brain Injury (MTBI) Screening
content: Access tool to identify Service Members who may need further evaluation for MTBI.

title: National Council on Disability - Report on the Invisible Wounds of TBI & PTSD
content: Describes the less visible psychological and neurological injuries associated with post traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) or traumatic brain injury (TBI). Download a report titled Invisible Wounds: Serving Service Members and Veterans with PTSD and TBI.

title: National Institute of Neurological Disorders & Stroke (NINDS) Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) Information Page
content: Find organizations that can help people live with TBI.

title: National Resource Center for Traumatic Brain Injury
content: Provides fact sheet and other information about TBI that is available free of charge.

title: Outreach Center for Psychological Health & Traumatic Brain Injury
content: Contact the 24-hour/7 days a week outreach center at 866-966-1020 to reach the Defense Centers of Excellence for Psychological Health and Traumatic Brain Injury (DCoE).

title: Real Warriors Campaign
content: Find articles and resources on a variety of psychological health issues, as well as video interviews with Service Members, their families and others dealing with mental health issues and traumatic brain injuries.

title: Rehabilitation Research & Training Center (RRTC) on Community Integration of Persons with Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)
content: Provides information and resources to help people affected by TBI, their families and professionals who work with and treat them in order to maximize their access to services and their participation in their communities.

title: Resources for Veterans & Their Families on Traumatic Brain Injury
content: Get information from the National Association of State Head Injury Administrators on TBI, including state, local and federal resources.

title: Thomas Jerome House
content: Provides permanent residential care to Veterans with traumatic brain injury, offering on-site 24 hour-a-day care where Service Members with traumatic brain injuries and their assistants, live together as family.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) & Stroke Rehabilitation (TSR) Program
content: Provides easy access to the most current information about NICHD research projects, publications, news releases and other activities related to TBI and TSR and similar disorders.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury - The Journey Home
content: Provides military personnel, patients, family members and caregivers with information on the types and symptoms of brain injury, TBI treatment and recovery and helpful insights about the potential long-term effects of brain injury.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury Resource Directory (TBIRD)
content: Offers information and resources available on a range of topics related to TBI that is produced by the Rehabilitation Research Center at Santa Clara Valley Medical Center.

title: Defense Brain Injury Center
content: Serving active duty members their beneficiaries, and veterans with traumatic brain injuries (TBIs), the Defense Brain Injury Center seeks to improve lives through state-of-the-art clinical care, innovative clinical research initiatives and educational programs.The Defense Brain Injury Center is a component of the Defense Centers of Excellence.

title: Defense & Veterans Brain Injury Center (DVBIC)
content: Learn about the traumatic brain injury (TBI) programs in DoD and VA hospitals and civilian TBI rehabilitation programs. These DVBIC sites work together to provide and improve TBI care.

title: The Arms Forces
content: Provides education and programs that allow Veterans with traumatic brain injury or post-traumatic stress disorder to be more easily understood and live a higher quality of life. Includes a network of trained volunteer Life Navigation Coaches who mentor and give individual assistance at no cost to the Veteran and the LEEF family support experience.

title: What is TBI?
content: Provides a definition of traumatic brain injury, a screening tool and information on resources for healing and treatment.

title: Operation Mend
content: Provides medical services to military personnel wounded during service in Iraq and Afghanistan and offers Buddy Families who share their homes with the Service Members during their time in Los Angeles.

title: Achieving Vocational Success After TBI
content: Read an important article on how to ease the return to work, school or homemaking after suffering a traumatic brain injury.

title: Higher Ground
content: Rehabilitation program that combines sports, family and coping therapies to restore and rehabilitate Service Members.  Specializes in serving Veterans with traumatic brain injuries (TBI), post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), polytrauma, blindness, and mental illness and offers a three year follow-up care plan for all participants.

title: Navy Safe Harbor Case Management
content: Assigns a care professional to help sailors and Coast Guardsmen identify short- and long-term goals and develop plans to achieve them. Also anticipates and addresses the day-to-day non-medical needs of enrolled Service Members and their families and works to resolve any problems that arise during recovery.

title: Brain Injury Dialogues
content: Learn more about a documentary following the lives of people living with traumatic brain injuries.

title: Veterans Studies at the Center for BrainHealth
content: Searches for ways to promote brain health and fitness across the entire human lifespan, through brain research and practical clinical applications. Specific Service Member-related research initiatives underway focus on post-traumatic stress disorder, traumatic brain injury and improving response times in highly stressful environments.

title: Family of a Vet - Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) Resources
content: Provides information on Traumatic Brain Injury including symptoms and coping skills.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury - An Overview
content: Access an interactive learning module from the Center on Brain Injury Research & Training to learn about traumatic brain injury. The module provides some basic facts about traumatic brain injury and how it affects people.

title: 5 Things You Need to Know About Concussions
content: Access information about this common head injury from the Defense Centers of Excellence.

title: Make the Connection
content: Connects Veterans, their friends and family members with information, resources, and solutions to issues affecting their health, well-being and everyday lives. Hear inspiring stories of strength, learn what has worked for other Veterans and explore information about physical and mental health symptoms, challenging life events and mental health conditions.

title: BrainLine Military
content: Find information about traumatic brain injury (TBI) for the military community from  Brainline.org.

title: TBI Webcasts
content: Find informative webcasts about traumatic brain injury's effect on other health topics.

title: Brain Injury Clinical Research at CNRM
content: Find out more about research studies enrolling participants. The Center for Neuroscience and Regenerative Medicine (CNRM) is a federal medical research program to improve the understanding of traumatic brain injury (TBI) and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD). Most research takes place at the National Institutes of Health (NIH) and National Naval Medical Center in Bethesda, MD and Walter Reed Army Medical Center in Washington, DC.

title: Resurrecting Lives Foundation
content: Assists Veterans with traumatic brain injury (TBI) by raising awareness of and funding for research, treatment, advocacy and  education of TBI.

title: Brain Injury Recovery Network

content: Details mental health services are available to Veterans at local and regional VA health care facilities.

title: mTBI Mechanisms of Action of HBO2 for Persistent Post-Concussive Symptoms (BIMA)
content: Investigates the mechanisms of action of hyperbaric oxygen therapy for persistent post-concussive symptoms after mild traumatic brain injury and is sponsored the Office of the Surgeon General, Department of the Army.

Provides medically prescribed prosthetic and sensory aids to eligible veterans. These aids include artificial limbs, hearing aids, communication aids, eyeglasses, orthopedic braces and shoes, wheelchairs, crutches and canes.
For additional information, contact the prosthetic representative at the nearest VA medical center or outpatient clinic.

content: Find information on health care for Veterans and their families, clinical trials, research studies, risk factors, disability compensation and outreach.

title: Chronic Fatigue Syndrome (CFS)
content: Learn about the Centers for Disease Control's CFS Research Program assessing The Health Impact of Chemical Exposures During the Gulf War.

title: Gulf War Deployments - Particulates
content: Provides information on the occurrence and health consequences of exposure to oil well fires during the Gulf War. Includes links to other information and resources, including a report on exposure to particulates during the Persian Gulf War and another Environmental Exposure Report on particulate matter.

title: Gulf War Veterans' Health - Medical Evaluation of a U.S. Cohort
content: Read a study showing Gulf War deployment is associated with increased risk of skin conditions.

title: Gulf War Veterans' Illnesses
content: Provides information for Veterans, their families and others about VA health care programs related to Operations Desert Shield, Desert Storm and Iraqi Freedom. Includes other publications about health issues associated with deployment in the Persian Gulf.  To locate the nearest VA Medical Center or for general health questions related to Gulf service, call the VA Gulf War Veterans Information Helpline at 1-800-PGW-VETS.

title: GulfLINK - Office of the Special Assistant for Gulf War Illnesses
content: Provides online access to medical and other documents from the 1990-1991 Gulf War in order to provide Service Members, Veterans and others with information on possible health effects of Gulf War service. The site also includes a link to medical information, including medical evaluation programs, medical records and relevant medical research and publications.

title: Health Outcomes & Concerns - Asthma Concerns Due to Oil-Fire-Smoke
content: Provides information of particular relevance to Gulf War Veterans regarding the respiratory and other effects of exposure to burning oil wells. Also includes a link to a summary of available information on health consequences of exposure.

title: Institute of Medicine Projects & Reports Related to the U.S. Military & Veterans
content: Contains a list of current projects and reports concerning the U.S. military and Veterans, including the Institute of Medicine's work on Agent Orange and Gulf War Syndrome.

title: Research Advisory Committee Report on Gulf War Veterans' Illnesses
content: Learn about the VA's research advisory committee that makes recommendations regarding medical research on Gulf War illnesses by the U.S. government.

title: VA Research Advisory Committee on Gulf War Illnesses - Links
content: Provides links to reports and government sites on Gulf War Illnesses from VA, DoD, National Institutes of Health and Centers for Disease Control. Links contain studies about illnesses connected to the Gulf War as well as to government offices with resources on Gulf War Illnesses.

title: VA Special Health Registry Examination Programs
content: Provides information on health registries for eligible Veterans to determine if health problems may be related to environmental exposures during military service. Registries include Gulf War, depleted uranium, Agent Orange and ionizing radiation.

title: War-Related Injury & Illness Study Centers (WRIISCs)
content: Provides specialized health care, research, education and outreach for combat Veterans with difficult to diagnose conditions, including Gulf War Illness.

title: Guide to Today's Toxic Wars
content: Read about the history of Gulf War Illness, its effects on Service Members and Veterans and resources to get help. A resource of the National Gulf War Resource Center.

title: Gulf War Registry Health Exam
content: Find information about the Gulf War Registry, a VA program to track the special health concerns of Veterans who served in the Gulf during Operation Desert Shield, Operation Desert Storm, Operation Iraqi Freedom or Operation New Dawn.

title: Gulf War Veterans' Illnesses Biorepository
content: Supports research on the causes, progression and treatment of disorders affecting Veterans of the 1990-1991 Gulf War through mailed surveys, telephone calls, and electronic health records.

title: Chemical Warfare - Blister Agents
content: Provides information and fact sheets on blister agents, including Mustard Gas, that can cause respiratory problems after exposure.

title: Chemical-Biological (CB) Warfare Exposures Web Site
content: Provides Service Members, Veterans, their families and the public with information on what happened during CB testing conducted years ago that potentially affected the health of those who served.

title: Deployment Health Clinical Center (DHCC) Gulf War Deployments - Environmental Exposures
content: Provides information on insecticides commonly used in the Gulf, acute symptoms of exposure and clinical significance.

title: Deployment Health Clinical Center - Emerging Health Conditions
content: Lists health conditions of particular relevance to Operations Enduring Freedom and Iraqi Freedom, including such respiratory conditions as Acute Eosinophilic Pneumonia, Anthrax, Influenza, Severe Acute Respiratory Syndrome (SARS) and Tuberculosis. Also includes links to additional information and treatment resources.

title: Diseases of Military Significance
content: Download a brochure describing infections that can be spread by people, insects and animals - often following a Service Member's return from active duty.

title: Leishmaniasis Fact Sheet
content: Discusses prevention strategies related to military personnel and leishmaniasis, a disease caused by a parasite spread through sand fly bites. Leishmaniasis has been reported in military personnel deployed in Iraq and Afghanistan during Operations Enduring Freedom and Iraqi Freedom, and in Kuwait and elsewhere during the Persian Gulf War.

title: Leishmaniasis Information
content: Answers to frequently asked questions about leishmaniasis, a parasitic disease spread by the bite of infected sand flies.

title: Leptospirosis - Frequently Asked Questions
content: Provides information about Leptospirosis, which is a disease caused by exposure to contaminated water.

title: Medically Unexplained Physical Symptoms (MUPS) - A Guide for Re-Deploying Service Members
content: Provides examples of MUPS, information on what the military health care community is doing about MUPS and advice for Service Members or Veterans who experience troublesome physical symptoms after a deployment.

title: U.S. Army Center for Health Promotion & Preventive Medicine - Asbestos Fact Sheet
content: Discusses the health effects, signs and symptoms of exposure to asbestos, as well as methods of prevention.

title: U.S. Army Center for Health Promotion & Preventive Medicine - Facts About Leptospirosis
content: Facts and frequently asked questions about Leptospirosis, which is caused by exposure to contaminated water.

title: U.S. Army Center for Health Promotion & Preventive Medicine - Particulate Matter (PM) Air Pollution Exposures During Military Deployments
content: Discusses the sources of PM air pollution likely encountered during military deployments, as well as the health effects of exposure.

title: Health & Wellbeing for Ground Zero Workers & Volunteers
content: Offers workers and volunteers at Ground Zero a free immune-building detoxification program. The goal is to reach recovery workers and volunteers who are struggling with health issues because of exposure to the sites.

title: VA Environmental Agents Service
content: Provides information for Veterans, their families and others about VA health care programs related to environmental issues.

title: VA Special Health Registry Examination Programs
content: Provides information on health registries for eligible Veterans to determine if health problems may be related to environmental exposures during military service. Registries include Gulf War, depleted uranium, Agent Orange and ionizing radiation.

title: VA Environmental Hazards: Burn Pits
content: Provides information about potential exposure to toxins from burn pits, possible health-related problems and VA benefits.

title: DAV Burn Pit Action Center
content: Addresses the concerns of Service Members, Veterans, their families and others about the damages of the burn pits in Iraq and Afghanistan.

title: Agent Orange & Chloracne Information Brief

title: Agent Orange & Chronic Lymphocytic Leukemia
content: Discusses the most common of the four primary forms of leukemia and the association with exposure to Agent Orange by Vietnam Veterans.  Includes conclusions from the National Academy of Sciences and where a Veteran can get more information on the subject.

title: Agent Orange & Hodgkin's Disease
content: Discusses malignant lymphoma (a type of cancer), which is characterized by progressive enlargement of the lymph nodes, liver and spleen, and anemia, and its association with exposure to Agent Orange by Vietnam Veterans.  Includes conclusions  from the National Academy of Sciences and where a Veteran can get more information on the subject.

title: Agent Orange & Multiple Myeloma
content: Discusses a form of cancer in specific bone marrow cells called the plasma cell and the association with exposure to Agent Orange by Vietnam Veterans.  Includes conclusions from the National Academy of Sciences and where a Veteran can get more information on the subject.

title: Agent Orange & Non-Hodgkin's Lymphoma
content: Discusses malignant tumors that affect the lymph glands and other lymphatic tissue and the association with exposure to Agent Orange by Vietnam Veterans.  Includes conclusions from the National Academy of Sciences and where a Veteran can get more information on the subject.

title: Agent Orange & Prostate Cancer
content: Describes how prostate cancer is detected and treated and the potential connection between exposure to Agent Orange and an increased risk of getting prostate cancer.

title: Agent Orange & Respiratory Cancers
content: Discusses carcinomas of the lung, larynx, trachea and bronchus and the association with exposure to Agent Orange by Vietnam Veterans.  Includes conclusions from the National Academy of Sciences and where a Veteran can get more information on the subject.

title: Agent Orange & Soft Tissue Sarcomas
content: Discusses malignant tumors (cancer) that arise from body tissues such as muscle, fat, blood and lymph vessels and connective tissues (that is, distinct from hard tissue such as bone or cartilage), and their association with exposure to Agent Orange by Vietnam Veterans.  Includes conclusions from the National Academy of Sciences and where a Veteran can get more information on the subject.

title: Agent Orange & Type II Diabetes
content: Discusses the link between Agent Orange and Type II diabetes in Vietnam Veterans.

title: Agent Orange Fact Sheets from the VA
content: Designed to help Vietnam Veterans, their families and others concerned about the possible health effects from exposure to herbicides during the Vietnam War.

title: Institute of Medicine Projects & Reports Related to the U.S. Military & Veterans
content: Contains a list of current projects and reports concerning the U.S. military and Veterans, including the Institute of Medicine's work on Agent Orange and Gulf War Syndrome.

title: Overview of Leishmaniasis
content: Overview of all three forms of leishmaniasis, which is transmitted by the bites of infected sand flies.

content: Provides information for Veterans, their families and others about VA health care programs related to Agent Orange.

title: VA Special Health Registry Examination Programs
content: Provides information on health registries for eligible Veterans to determine if health problems may be related to environmental exposures during military service. Registries include Gulf War, depleted uranium, Agent Orange and ionizing radiation.

content: Provides resources and support to injured Service Members, Veterans and their families, especially those who have sustained the hidden injuries of war.

content: Access a DoD program that works to improve psychological health and TBI treatment of Service Members and Veterans.

content: Provides a Self Assessment for Veterans service that is voluntary and anonymous, and is offered online, by phone and through special events held at installations and reserve units.

title: Mental Health America (MHA) Affiliate Directory
content: Contact the local MHA affiliates in your state that can help you find support groups in your area.

title: Mental Health Resources for Returning Veterans & Their Families
content: Access information from the Substance Abuse & Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) about prevention, treatment and recovery support for mental health and substance use disorders.

title: Mental Health Screening Tool
content: Access self-assessments for depression, bipolar disorder, alcohol use, post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and generalized anxiety disorder.

content: Find information on PTSD from NAMI, including symptoms, treatment and available resources.

title: VA National Center for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Advances the clinical care and well-being of America's Veterans through research, education and training in the science, diagnosis and treatment of PTSD and stress-related disorders.

title: National Institute of Mental Health - Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) Research Study
content: Call 1-866-627-6464 to participate in one of several research studies underway relating to PTSD.

title: Outreach Center for Psychological Health & Traumatic Brain Injury

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Find information from the Vietnam Veterans of America on PTSD, including how to get help and tips on working with service providers.

content: Access a resource from the National Institute of Mental Health that explains what PTSD is, when it starts, how long it lasts and how to get help.

content: Answers commonly asked questions about the effects of trauma, including basic information about PTSD and other common reactions.

title: Returning from the War Zone - A Guide for Military Personnel
content: Helps Service Members and Veterans understand what to expect when returning from a war zone, how to handle the transition, the signs of post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and where to go for help.

content: Researches, develops, evaluates, and deploys new and existing technologies for Psychological Health (PH) and Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) across the Department of Defense (DoD).

title: VA - Mental Health - Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)

title: Vet Centers
content: Offers readjustment counseling and outreach services to Veterans who served in any combat zone. Services are also available for family members on military-related issues.

title: VetAdvisor Support Program: Telephonic & Behavioral Health Screening & Treatment
content: Provides outreach and screening to Veterans for behavioral issues that might otherwise go unrecognized and unresolved.

title: War Zone Related Stress Reactions - What Veterans Need to Know
content: Describes how and why traumatic war experiences often cause reactions in Veterans.

title: War Related Illness and Injury Study Center (WRIISC)
content: Provides information on Post Traumatic Stress Disorder. Gives treatment options through the Department of Veterans Affairs.

title: The Soldiers Project
content: Access free, confidential mental health counseling services for Veterans, Service Members and their families.

title: RESPECT-Mil Treatment Model
content: RESPECT-Mil is a treatment model designed by the United States Department of Defenses Deployment Health Clinical Center (DHCC) to screen, assess and treat active duty Soldiers with depression and/or PTSD.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) - Research Fact Sheet
content: Find information from the National Institute of Mental Health on research efforts related to risk factors for PTSD.

title: American Combat Veterans of War (ACVOW)
content: Recruits combat Veteran volunteers to mentor, coach and assist warriors suffering from combat stress, allowing them and their families to lead productive and fulfilling lives. Offers support services for Veterans, women Veterans and the family.

title: inTransition
content: Facing a change in status, orders or returning to civilian life? A new program from the Defense Centers of Excellence (DCoE) can help make the transition between mental health providers easier. For 24 hour help and information call 1-800-424-7877

title: Higher Ground
content: Rehabilitation program that combines sports, family and coping therapies to restore and rehabilitate Service Members.  Specializes in serving Veterans with traumatic brain injuries (TBI), post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), polytrauma, blindness, and mental illness and offers a three year follow-up care plan for all participants.

title: Vets Prevail
content: Find information on battling post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and depression through this program for Veterans by Veterans. Interactive training is delivered online, providing a convenient and confidential approach to treating deployment-related effects of combat such as PTSD, depression and anxiety.

title: The Military Wellness Program at Holliswood Hospital
content: Provides intensive, evidence-based treatments for posttraumatic stress disorders, depression, anxiety, anger management problems, and substance misuse issues in Service Members, Veterans and their families.

title: Navy Safe Harbor Case Management
content: Assigns a care professional to help sailors and Coast Guardsmen identify short- and long-term goals and develop plans to achieve them. Also anticipates and addresses the day-to-day non-medical needs of enrolled Service Members and their families and works to resolve any problems that arise during recovery.

title: The Arms Forces
content: Provides education and programs that allow Veterans with traumatic brain injury or post-traumatic stress disorder to be more easily understood and live a higher quality of life. Includes a network of trained volunteer Life Navigation Coaches who mentor and give individual assistance at no cost to the Veteran and the LEEF family support experience.

title: Veterans Studies at the Center for BrainHealth
content: Searches for ways to promote brain health and fitness across the entire human lifespan, through brain research and practical clinical applications. Specific Service Member-related research initiatives underway focus on post-traumatic stress disorder, traumatic brain injury and improving response times in highly stressful environments.

title: Defense Centers of Excellence - Podcasts
content: Find and listen to podcasts on a variety of topics from the Defense Centers of Excellence. Podcast topics include mental health, brain injury, information for caregivers and helping children understand their parent's injury.

title: Wounded Warrior Project - Restore Warriors
content: Provides a self-assessment to help identify problem areas and supply feedback and recommendations for self-help exercises. Also contains online training exercises and professional help locators.

title: Family of a Vet - Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) Resources
content: Provides information on Post Traumatic Stress including symptoms and treatments.

title: TRICARE - Behavioral Health Care Services
content: Provides information on health care services available through TRICARE during times of stress, depression, grief and anxiety.

title: Brain Injury Clinical Research at CNRM
content: Find out more about research studies enrolling participants. The Center for Neuroscience and Regenerative Medicine (CNRM) is a federal medical research program to improve the understanding of traumatic brain injury (TBI) and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD). Most research takes place at the National Institutes of Health (NIH) and National Naval Medical Center in Bethesda, MD and Walter Reed Army Medical Center in Washington, DC.

title: National Intrepid Center of Excellence (NICoE)
content: Provides evaluation, treatment planning, research and education dedicated to providing care to Service Members and families dealing with traumatic brain injuries and psychological health conditions.

title: Moving Forward
content: Operates a free, on-line educational and life coaching program from the VA that teaches problem solving skills to help better handle life’s challenges.

title: VA PTSD Coach Online
content: Offers simple exercises, tools and strategies for coping with symptoms of post-traumatic stress disorder. Provided by the VA National Center for PTSD.

title: MilitaryFamily.com PTSD Information
content: Find information on Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) and tips for coping with the illness.

title: Veterans Living with PTSD
content: Access information on support for Veterans living with post traumatic stress disorder. Locate other resources for those dealing with depression and bipolar disorder.

title: Make the Connection
content: Connects Veterans, their friends and family members with information, resources, and solutions to issues affecting their health, well-being and everyday lives. Hear inspiring stories of strength, learn what has worked for other Veterans and explore information about physical and mental health symptoms, challenging life events and mental health conditions.

title: Coaching Into Care
content: Provides coaching to the family members and friends of Veterans to assist them in supporting their loved ones during post-deployment and ongoing reintegration. This is a national clinical service providing information and assistance. For confidential help, call 1-888-823-7458.

title: Guide to VA Mental Health Services for Veterans & Families
content: Details mental health services are available to Veterans at local and regional VA health care facilities.

title: Living With Traumatic Stress - You Are Not Alone
content: A booklet from Disabled American Veterans for Service Members, Veterans and their families dealing with traumatic stress.

title: Effects of PTSD on the Family
content: Discusses the impact of PTSD on the family. A shorter version is also available.

title: Talk Therapy Television
content: Watch videos about the challenges facing returning veterans and their families. Learn about when to get help for mental illness, the kinds of treatment available and peer support groups.

content: Shares information to safeguard the health and well-being of Service Members and their families, and to sustain medical and rehabilitative care to the sick and injured anywhere in the world.

title: Mental Health Professionals for Veterans
content: Provides education and links to counselors treating returning servicemembers. Its Webinar on Treating Returning Servicemembers addresses steps necessary to provide trained counselors for veterans and their families.

title: Heads Up - Brain Injury in Your Practice Tool Kit
content: Access this physician's tool kit that improves clinical diagnosis and management of traumatic brain injury.

title: Mild Traumatic Brain Injury (MTBI) Screening
content: Access tool to identify Service Members who may need further evaluation for MTBI.

title: National Long Term Care Ombudsman Resource Center
content: Advocates for residents' rights and quality care, educates consumers and providers, resolves residents' complaints and provide information to the public; site includes links for locating local and state ombudsmen as well as resources for ombudsmen and volunteers.

title: A Clinician's Guide to Medications for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Provides information on PTSD symptoms, biological disturbances found in PTSD, and how and which kinds of medications help regulate these responses.

title: Medical Management of Biological Casualties Handbook - Seventh Edition
content: Provides concise supplemental reading material to assist health-care providers in the management of biological casualties.

title: Civilian Provider Education
content: Delivers post-traumatic stress disorder and traumatic brain injury (PTSD/TBI) education to civilian primary care and mental health providers.

title: Clinicians' Trauma Update (CTU)
content: Download a newsletter published by the National Center for PTSD that provides summaries of clinically relevant research publications including links to the full article or abstract.

title: Counseling Veteran Students
content: Learn about VA efforts to help campus professionals learn more about the adjustment challenges and problems Veteran students face and how to help them with the available VA resources and services.

title: Deployment Health & Readiness Library
content: Provides an A-Z listing of medical information and additional materials to assist clinicians and health care providers.

title: Depression in Primary Care
content: Learn about the impact of depression on members of the military and their families.

title: For Health Care Providers
content: Access an A-Z directory for specific medical conditions, deployment names by operation, deployment forms, technical guides and more.

title: Fostering Recovery - From Medical Illness, Injury & Disease
content: Download a fact sheet for military health providers on the importance of the recovery phase in sustaining the health of Service Members and their families.

title: Fostering Safety, Health & Preparedness for Military Medical Providers
content: Download a fact sheet from the Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences offers military medical providers helpful reminders to safeguard their patients and their families during times of transition including deployment, reunions and reintegration. Includes health care tips and disaster preparedness.

title: Helping National Guard & Reserve Reenter the Workplace
content: Explains the emotional and psychological issues that National Guard and Reserve Members may experience transitioning from active duty into their former job or workplace.

title: Homeless Veterans & Health Care - A Resource Guide for Providers
content: Access the National Health Care for the Homeless Council resource guide that addresses characteristics of homeless Veterans, clinical issues, eligibility criteria, health programs, benefits, homeless programs, critical access issues, non-VA resources, and collaboration and advocacy.

title: Iraq War Clinician Guide
content: Developed by members of the National Center for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder and the Department of Defense, this guide was created specifically for clinicians to address the unique needs of Veterans of the Iraq war.

title: National Guideline Clearinghouse (NGC)
content: Provides physicians, nurses, and other health professionals, health care providers, health plans, integrated delivery systems, purchasers and others an accessible mechanism for obtaining objective, detailed information on clinical practice guidelines and furthers their dissemination, implementation and use.

title: Reintegration Fact Sheet for Providers
content: Outlines a four-step guide on how couples can reestablish a shared sense of purpose following deployment. Accompanies Becoming A Couple Again.

title: Suicide Facts for Primary Care Providers
content: Fact sheet provides warning signs and risk factors associated with suicide.

title: Sustaining Health Care Continuity for Our Military Families
content: Learn how to reinforce and facilitate continuity of health care for families who have moved or are preparing to move.

title: Sexual Trauma: Information for Women's Medical Providers
content: Answers some common questions about sexual trauma and how it can impact a woman's physical and mental health.

title: Citizen Soldier Support Program (CSSP)
content: Provides on-site and online courses on PTSD & TBI, Women Returning from Combat and Family Issues to prepare civilian providers to address post deployment issues facing OIF/OEF Veterans and their families. CSSP also works with public and private organizations to increase access to trained behavioral health providers.

title: Post Deployment Health & Distress Responses
content: Find information about post-deployment health from the Center for the Study of Traumatic Stress .

title: Major Depressive Episode and Treatment for Depression Among Veterans Aged 21 to 39
content: Access a National Survey on Drug Use and Health report on depression and suicide amongst young Veterans.

title: Management of Substance Abuse Disorders
content: Presentation featureing information on best practices for treating substance abuse from the Veterans' Health Administration and the Department of Defense.

title: Male Veterans with Co-Occuring Serious Mental Illness & Substance Abuse Disorder
content: Access a National Survey on Drug Use and Health report on issues surrounding and treatment of co-occuring mental illness and substance abuse.

title: 5 Things You Need to Know About Concussions
content: Access information about this common head injury from the Defense Centers of Excellence.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury Task Force Information Paper
content: Read the findings on definition, screening and treatment of traumatic brain injury from the Traumatic Brain Injury Task Force.

title: War Within
content: Offers a network of primary and behavioral health care providers who are trained in, or who have expressed an interest in serving the specific needs of military members and their families.

title: VA National Center for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Advances the clinical care and well-being of America's Veterans through research, education and training in the science, diagnosis and treatment of PTSD and stress-related disorders.

title: Soldiers & Veterans Initiative (SVI)
content: An initiative of the American Psychoanalytic Association that adds a psychoanalytic voice to the mental health crisis among soldiers, Veterans and their families.  Includes information on what psychoanalysts are doing and upcoming events.

title: Adherence - Addressing a Range of Patient Health Behaviors
content: Download a fact sheet for health providers about ways to increase patient adherence to treatments and recommendations.

title: Psychological First Aid - Helping Victims in the Immediate Aftermath of Disaster
content: Provides for first responders an evidenced-based approach for helping victims cope in the immediate aftermath of a disaster.

title: Depression in Primary Care
content: Learn about the impact of depression on members of the military and their families.

title: Health Literacy: Addressing Communication Barriers to Foster Patient Self-Care & Family Care
content: Provides information on educating a patient about proper health care before the patient leaves the clinic, emergency room or office.

title: Fostering Safety, Health & Preparedness for Military Medical Providers
content: Download a fact sheet from the Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences offers military medical providers helpful reminders to safeguard their patients and their families during times of transition including deployment, reunions and reintegration. Includes health care tips and disaster preparedness.

title: Helping National Guard & Reserve Reenter the Workplace
content: Explains the emotional and psychological issues that National Guard and Reserve Members may experience transitioning from active duty into their former job or workplace.

title: Reintegration Fact Sheet for Providers
content: Outlines a four-step guide on how couples can reestablish a shared sense of purpose following deployment. Accompanies Becoming A Couple Again.

title: Iraq War Clinician Guide
content: Developed by members of the National Center for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder and the Department of Defense, this guide was created specifically for clinicians to address the unique needs of Veterans of the Iraq war.

title: Fostering Recovery - From Medical Illness, Injury & Disease
content: Download a fact sheet for military health providers on the importance of the recovery phase in sustaining the health of Service Members and their families.

title: Sustaining Health Care Continuity for Our Military Families
content: Learn how to reinforce and facilitate continuity of health care for families who have moved or are preparing to move.

title: Counseling Veteran Students
content: Learn about VA efforts to help campus professionals learn more about the adjustment challenges and problems Veteran students face and how to help them with the available VA resources and services.

title: Assessing PTSD for Compensation & Pension Examinations
content: Provides best practices, protocol and worksheets for assessing PTSD among Veterans for compensation and pension examinations.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) - Information for Mental Health Care Providers
content: Learn about treating PTSD in specific populations including ethnic minorities and persons with severe mental illness.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) 101
content: Access a Web-based curriculum for practitioners covering diverse topics related to combat stress/PTSD.

title: Systematic Approach to Social Work Practice - Working with Clients with Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)
content: Helps social workers feel more comfortable and confident in their clinical interactions with clients with brain injury, and to increase their knowledge about TBI.

title: Mental Health Professionals for Veterans
content: Provides education and links to counselors treating returning servicemembers. Its Webinar on Treating Returning Servicemembers addresses steps necessary to provide trained counselors for veterans and their families.

title: Detoxification & Substance Abuse Treatment Training Manual
content: Provides instruction to substance abuse treatment staff and related professionals and service providers about the Treatment Improvement Protocol (TIP) 45: Detoxification and Substance Abuse Treatment.

title: Federal Recovery Coordination Program for OEF/OIF Veterans
content: Find OEF and OIF Veterans programs and learn about eligibility and how care is coordinated among various clinics and treatment centers.

title: Center for Mind-Body Medicine
content: Works to create a more effective, comprehensive and compassionate model of health care and health education. Combines modern science with the world's healing traditions, to help health professionals heal themselves, their patients and clients, and their communities.

title: TRICARE - Handbooks
content: Find resources available to answer questions about TRICARE programs, policies and procedures, or if you need assistance coordinating care for a TRICARE beneficiary. Additional Online TRICARE Manuals are also available.

title: Military Cultural Competence
content: Access an online course from the Uniformed Services University of the Health Sciences. The course is intended to assist civilian mental health providers in better understanding, communicating and effectively interacting with Service members and their families

title: Understanding Military Culture when Treating PTSD
content: This 50 minute presentation distributed by the National Center on PTSD is aimed at helping providers learn more about military culture and PTSD in order to understand their patients better.

title: Care for the Troops Training Materials
content: Find information and training modules on a variety of topics and health concerns in the military community.

title: VA Veterans Health Initiative
content: Offers a course series developed by the Employee Education System to enhance clinician knowledge about war-related health outcomes and concerns. Includes courses on Vietnam Veterans and Agent Orange Exposure, Caring for War Wounded, A Guide to Gulf War Veterans' Health, Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder: Implications for Primary Care, Traumatic Brain Injury and more.

title: Altarum - Veterans Community Action Team
content: Find information on this initiative to improve Veteran care by optimizing the relationships between private, public and non-profit organizations.

title: American Association of Suicidology (AAS)
content: Promotes research, public awareness programs, public education and training for professionals and volunteers. In addition, AAS serves as a national clearinghouse for information on suicide.

title: American Congress of Rehabilitation Medicine
content: Promotes rehabilitative research that improves health, independence, productivity and quality of life for people with disabling conditions and facilitates information dissemination and the transfer of technology.

title: Brain Trauma Foundation
content: Improves the outcome of patients with traumatic brain injury (TBI) by developing best practice guidelines, conducting clinical research and educating medical personnel. Includes specific research and resources on TBI in the Military.

title: American Academy of Orthopaedic Surgeons (AAOS) - Extremity War Injuries & Disaster Preparedness
content: Supports several research events and programs partnering military orthopaedic surgeons to advance the care of the wounded warrior. Its annual symposia series, "Extremity War Injuries," has served to define current knowledge regarding management of extremity war injuries.

title: Center for the Study of Traumatic Stress
content: Lists resources and provides research relating to trauma and coping with traumatic events such as trauma training and education, terrorism preparedness and trauma consultations. The Center is a partner to the Defense Centers of Excellence for Psychological Health & Traumatic Brain Injury. Read the Center's military-related fact sheets.

title: Force Health Protection & Readiness
content: Shares information to safeguard the health and well-being of Service Members and their families, and to sustain medical and rehabilitative care to the sick and injured anywhere in the world.

title: Self-Disclosure & Its Impact on Individuals Who Receive Mental Health Services
content: Read a paper from the Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration (SAMHSA) examines the role self-disclosure plays in reducing stigma and discrimination associated with mental illness.

title: Gulf War Veterans with Anxiety - Prevalence, Co-morbidity & Risk Factors
content: Download a publication that addresses the frequency of anxiety in the military population and how it is more common among Gulf War veterans than non-deployed military personnel.

title: Agency for Healthcare Research and Quality (AHRQ)
content: Conducts research on health care quality, costs, outcomes, and patient safety. Supported a study on telepsychiatry (therapy with a psychiatrist via videoconferencing), which has proved helpful to Veterans suffering from combat-related post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), who live in rural or underserved areas.

title: Research Advisory Committee on Gulf War Veterans' Illnesses
content:
Read the conclusions of a congressionally mandated research on the foremost causes of Gulf War illness and describes characteristics of this condition and provides direction for future research urgently
needed to improve the health of Gulf War veterans.

title: Restless Leg Syndrome Foundation (RLS)
content: Works to increase awareness and improve treatments for RLS.

title: Soldiers & Veterans Initiative (SVI)
content: An initiative of the American Psychoanalytic Association that adds a psychoanalytic voice to the mental health crisis among soldiers, Veterans and their families.  Includes information on what psychoanalysts are doing and upcoming events.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury Model Systems National Data & Statistical Center (TBINDSC)
content: Provides technical assistance, training and methodological consultation to 16 TBIMS centers as they collect and analyze longitudinal data from people with TBI in their communities, and as they conduct research toward evidence-based TBI rehabilitation interventions.

title: U.S. Army Center for Health Promotion & Preventive Medicine (USACHPPM)
content: Provides a database of links to find additional data on topics including USACHPPM services and resources, common diseases, health tips and environmental safety, among others.

title: U.S. Army Medical Command
content: Offers information on military treatment facilities and research centers worldwide. Find a treatment facility near you.

title: U.S. Army Research Institute for the Behavioral & Social Sciences (ARI)
content: Provides the Army with technical expertise and analytical support, along with decision making techniques for soldiers and leaders. ARI keeps track of information on soldier and leader attitudes and concerns. Its research includes assessing and improving leader skills screening tools and enhancing leadership styles and skills.

title: Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) Technical Assistance Center
content: Access a learning, collaboration and benchmarking tool for grantees and others affiliated with the Federal Traumatic Brain Injury Program.

title: VA Center for Chronic Disease Outcomes Research
content: Conducts research intended primarily to improve the health care of Veterans. Areas covered include post traumatic stress disorder; polytrauma and blast-related injuries and other unique health issues facing Veterans of Operations Iraqi Freedom and Enduring Freedom; and substance use disorders (including tobacco).

title: Congressional Special Interest Medical Research Programs (CSI)
content: Learn about research programs addressing breast, prostate and ovarian cancers; Gulf War Illness; traumatic brain injury (TBI); military health; and other areas of medical research.

title: Defense Centers of Excellence (DCoE) for Psychological Health (PH) & Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI)
content: Find information about a national collaborative network led by DoD and VA to share knowledge on psychological health and TBI, enhance clinical and management approaches and serve the needs of warrior families.

title: DoD Deployment-Related Medical Research Program
content: Addresses the prevention, diagnosis, treatment and mitigation of deployment-related injuries and psychological health concerns of deployed military personnel.

title: Federal Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI) Program
content: Learn about a federal grant program administered by the Maternal and Child Health Bureau to help states enhance access to comprehensive and coordinated community-based services for individuals with TBI and their families.

title: Henry M. Jackson Foundation for the Advancement of Military Medicine
content: Conducts quality medical research and education programs, and administers education endowment funds for the U.S. military community.

title: Mental Illness Research, Education & Clinical Center
content: Focuses on improving research, clinical care and education to help those with mental illness. Veterans may be eligible to participate in clinical research projects.

title: VA Office of Research & Development (ORD)
content: Explores all phases of Veterans' healthcare needs and serves as a resource for VA-funded researchers and research staff to learn of new funding opportunities, updated guidance and deadlines.

title: Military Health System (MHS) Vital Signs
content: Access the MHS monthly news e-bulletin with information on upcoming events and activities, the latest medical research and relevant health care news. Subscribe here.

title: Military Infectious Diseases Research Program (MIDRP)
content: Stay current on MIDRP's current research efforts, including bacterial, viral and parasitic research on diarrhea prevention, meningitis, malaria, cutaneous leishmaniasis, HIV and other infectious diseases.

title: Military Operational Medicine Research Program (MOMRP)
content: Provides biomedical solutions that protect soldiers and enhance their performance in operational and training environments that include multiple stressors. MOMRP is a biomedical research program with a problem-solving orientation and a human physiology research focus.

title: War Related Illness and Injury Study Center (WRIISC) - Information for Provider Referrals
content: Developes and provides expertise in post-deployment health for Veterans and their health care providers.

title: ClinicalTrials.gov
content: Find a registry of federally and privately supported clinical trials conducted in the United States and around the world. Although there are many definitions of clinical trials, they are generally considered to be biomedical or health-related research studies in human beings that follow a pre-defined protocol.

title: DeployMed ResearchLINK
content: Presents information on deployment medical research conducted and supported by federal research programs within DoD, VA and HHS. This Web site is a central resource of information on federally funded medical research related to deployments from the 1990-91 Gulf War forward.

title: Deployment Health Clinical Center (DHCC) Clinical & Health Services Research
content: Find information on DHCC's wide range of research projects designed to scientifically evaluate health services for post-deployment medical concerns.

title: Future of Military Health Care
content: Recommends changes that would help improve the military health care services being provided to members of the Armed Forces, retirees and their families.

title: Hyperbaric Oxygen Therapy (HBOT) Research Report
content: Provides a guide to the strengths and limitations of the evidence about the use of HBOT to treat patients who have brain injury, cerebral palsy and stroke.

title: Institute of Medicine Research on TBI
content: Read a report from the Committee on Gulf War and Health about the long-term consequences of Traumatic Brain Injury (TBI).

title: Invisible Wounds of War Monograph
content: Download the RAND Corporation study on post-traumatic stress disorder, depression and traumatic brain injury and find information on post-deployment stress and what families can do.

title: Military Medical Digest
content: Link to national and world health news from DoD's Military Health System.

title: National Institute of Mental Health - Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) Research Study
content: Call 1-866-627-6464 to participate in one of several research studies underway relating to PTSD.

title: National Institute on Drug Abuse Report on Comorbidity
content: Presents research on comorbidity, when two disorders or illnesses, specifically, addiction and other mental illnesses, occur in the same person. Covers how common these disorders are, why they co-occur, how they can diagnosed and treatment.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) - Research Fact Sheet
content: Find information from the National Institute of Mental Health on research efforts related to risk factors for PTSD.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) Clinical Trials
content: Learn about clinical trials and studies related to PTSD from the National Institute of Mental Health.

title: Published International Literature on Traumatic Stress (PILOTS)
content: Access an electronic index to the worldwide literature on post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) and other mental-health consequences due to exposure to traumatic events produced by the National Center for PTSD.

title: National Council on Disability - Report on the Invisible Wounds of TBI & PTSD
content: Describes the less visible psychological and neurological injuries associated with post traumatic stress disorder (PTSD) or traumatic brain injury (TBI). Download a report titled Invisible Wounds: Serving Service Members and Veterans with PTSD and TBI.

title: Study on How Mental Trauma Led to Illness in Veterans
content: Research study examining links between mental trauma and physical disease among Veterans of the Civil War and how the findings could apply to today's Veterans.

title: Warfighters Head Injury Study
content: Examines the long-term outcome of brain injuries, the effects of treatment on outcome and the effects of brain injury on people's behavior and abilities.

title: Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) - Clinical Practice Guidelines
content: Learn about the VA/DoD guidelines for the treatment of PTSD and download a pocket guide on acute stress disorder.

title: RESPECT-Mil Treatment Model
content: RESPECT-Mil is a treatment model designed by the United States Department of Defenses Deployment Health Clinical Center (DHCC) to screen, assess and treat active duty Soldiers with depression and/or PTSD.

title: Clinicians' Trauma Update (CTU)
content: Download a newsletter published by the National Center for PTSD that provides summaries of clinically relevant research publications including links to the full article or abstract.

title: Institute of Medicine Study on the Long-Term Consequences of Brain Injury
content: Read the Institute of Medicine's assessment on the possible long-term health outcomes of traumatic brain injury (TBI)that details outcomes that might be associated with mild, moderate, and severe injuries including neurologic, endocrine, psychologic outcomes, in addition to problems with social functioning.

title: National Center for Disaster Mental Health Research (NCDMHR)
content: Established to study how disasters, such as Hurricane Ike, in Galveston, TX, affect mental health, and to provide rapid response after such disasters.

title: National Center on Sleep Disorder Research (NCSDR)
content: Provides research, training, technology transfer and coordination related to various sleep disorders, including sleep apnea, narcolepsy, insomnia, parasomnia, jet-lag syndrome and disturbed biological and circadian rhythms.

title: National Health Foundation
content: Works to improve and enhance the healthcare of the underserved by developing and supporting innovative programs that 1) can become independently viable, 2) provide systemic solutions to gaps in healthcare access and delivery, and 3) have the potential to be replicated nationally.

title: National Institute on Disability and Rehabilitation Research
content: Supports a comprehensive program of research related to the rehabilitation of individuals with disabilities towards improving the lives of individuals with disabilities from birth through adulthood.

title: Naval Health Research Center (NHRC)
content: Serves as a leading medical research laboratory for DoD and the United States Navy. NHRC promotes, protects and maintains the health of USN and USMC personnel and beneficiaries through biomedical research, and supports the medical readiness of the armed services.

title: Psychological Health & Traumatic Brain Injury (PH/TBI) Research Program
content: Provides research funding to complement ongoing DoD efforts to ensure the health and readiness of our military forces and to support the Defense Centers of Excellence for Psychological Health and Traumatic Brain Injury in its efforts to advance and spread PH/TBI knowledge, enhance clinical and management approaches and facilitate other vital services to best serve the needs of warrior families impacted by PH problems and/or TBI.

title: Quality of Life Plus
content: Identifies the challenges of those who have been injured and works with teams of university students and faculty to solve these challenges so individuals with disabilities can live, work and play unassisted.

title: Joining Forces - Caring for Our Returning Military
content: Watch several online videos about the challanges Veterans and Service Members face returning from war zones, and their unique healthcare needs.

title: Trauma Informed Care for Women Veterans Experiencing Homelessness
content: Commissioned by the U.S. Department of Labor (DOL) Women's Bureau (WB) as one of its many efforts to help women veterans who are experiencing homelessness find jobs and successfully reintegrate back to civilian life.

title: Military and Veterans' Healthcare
content: Information and statistics on the health care of military personnel and Veterans.

title: Telemedicine & Advance Technology Research Center
content: Performs medical reconnaissance and special operations to address critical gaps that are underrepresented in DoD medical research programs.

title: The Center for Deployment Psychology
content: Find information and training modules for military and civilian psychologists, psychology interns/residents and other behavioral health professionals to provide high quality deployment-related behavioral health services to military personnel and their families.

title: Summa Health System - Center for The Treatment & Study of Traumatic Stress
content: Provides clinical services to Service Members, Veterans, families, and caregivers who are dealing with post-traumatic stress disorder, depression, or other difficulties related to stressful military or civilian experiences.

title: The Institute of HeartMath Resilience Programs for the Military
content: Conducts research and provides education to help people reduce stress, self-regulate emotions, and build energy and resiliency through tools, technology and training.

title: VA National Center for Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Advances the clinical care and well-being of America's Veterans through research, education and training in the science, diagnosis and treatment of PTSD and stress-related disorders.

title: VA - Mental Health - Post-Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD)
content: Learn the basics of what Post Traumatic Stress Disorder (PTSD) is, and find out how you can get help from the VA and other locations.

title: Penn State Clearinghouse for Military Family Readiness (CMFR)
content: Provides information, education and training, and technical assistance designed to increase the use of evidence-based programs and quality practices with military families.

title: Caring for Veterans Returning from Recent Conflicts
content: Learn about a conference series for VA health care professionals about the health concerns, diagnosis, treatment and research for Veterans returning from Iraq and Afghanistan. Includes mental health, infectious disease, exposure concerns, benefits, clinical practice guidelines, traumatic injury and more.

title: American Academy of Family Physicians
content: Works to to preserve and promote the science and art of Family Medicine and to ensure high-quality, cost-effective health care for patients of all ages.

title: American Speech Language Hearing Association (ASHA)
content: Supports speech-language pathologists, audiologists and language scientists by advocating on behalf of persons with communication and related disorders.

title: National Aphasia Association (NAA)
content: Non-profit organization that promotes public education, research, rehabilitation and support services to assist people with aphasia and their families.

title: Association of Military Surgeons of the United States (AMSUS)
content: Comprised of professionals serving in the full spectrum of health care disciplines in the Army, Navy, Air Force, Public Health Service, VA, Army Reserve, Navy Reserve, Air Force Reserve, Army National Guard, Air National Guard and the Coast Guard.

title: American Academy of Physical Medicine & Rehabilitation
content: Find information about a national medical society of nerve, muscle, bone and brain rehabilitation experts who treat injury or illness nonsurgically to decrease pain and restore function.

title: American Medical Rehabilitation Providers Association
content: Advocates for the needs of people with disabilities in their medical rehabilitation recovery.

title: American Kinesiotherapy Association (AKTA)
content: Encourages the use of medically prescribed therapeutic activities including exercise techniques and psychology of medically oriented exercise science.

title: American Academy of Neurology
content: Promotes care for patients with neurological disorders.

title: American Association of Colleges of Podiatric Medicine (AACPM)
content: Serves as a resource to students, residents and practitioners by providing direct access to academic institutions, highlighting opportunities for clerkships/residencies and linking students to mentors that guide their career development.

title: American Congress of Rehabilitation Medicine
content: Promotes rehabilitative research that improves health, independence, productivity and quality of life for people with disabling conditions and facilitates information dissemination and the transfer of technology.

title: American Nurses Association
content: Fosters high standards of nursing practice and promotes the rights of nurses in the workplace.

title: American Occupational Therapy Association, Inc.
content: Represents the interests and concerns of occupational therapy practitioners and students of occupational therapy. Works to improve consumer access to health care services and quality of occupational therapy services and promotes the professional development of members.

title: American Psychiatric Association
content: Works to ensure humane care and effective treatment for persons with mental disorders, including mental retardation and substance-related disorders.

title: American Psychological Association
content: Works to advance psychology as a science and profession and as a means of promoting health, education and human welfare.

title: American Therapeutic Recreation Association
content: Provide treatment and recreational services to restore, remediate or rehabilitate functioning and independence in persons with illnesses or disabling conditions.

title: Association of Academic Physiatrists
content: Promotes the advancement of teaching and research in physical medicine and rehabilitation within an academic environment.

title: Caring Bridge - Non-profit Partners
content: Offers free, personalized Web sites that provide valuable resources for families facing cancer, premature birth, heart disease, or any serious medical situation. It also partners with non-profit organizations that offer additional helpful resources on health care.

title: Case Management Society of America
content: Informs consumers and educates physicians, other providers, payors and regulators about improved patient outcomes through the services case and care managers provide.

title: Commission on Accreditation of Rehabilitation Facilities
content: Accredits human service providers in the areas of aging, behavioral health, child and youth services, employment, community outreach, medical rehabilitation and opioid treatment programs.

title: Hearing Loss Association of America
content: Provides people with hearing loss information, education, advocacy and support. Learn more about HLAA's partnership with the National Technical Institute for the Deaf at Rochester Institute of Technology to address the educational needs of Veterans of recent conflicts. Veterans of OIF and OEF are offered a complimentary one-year membership in HLAA.

title: Mercy Medical Airlift
content: Provides long-distance charitable medical air transportation, including additional charitable flight services.

title: National Association for the Advancement of Orthotics & Prosthetics
content: Shapes health care legislation and regulation for better O&P education, advocacy and technology.

title: National Association of County Behavioral Health & Developmental Disability Directors
content: National voice for county and local behavioral health and developmental disability authorities. Promotes national policies that recognize and support the critical role counties play in caring for people affected by mental illness, addiction and developmental disabilities.

title: National Association of Social Workers
content: Works to enhance the professional growth and development of its professional social worker members, to create and maintain professional standards and to advance sound social policies.

title: National Association of State Mental Health Program Directors
content: Represents state executives responsible for the $29.5 billion public mental health service delivery system in all 50 states, four territories and the District of Columbia.  Members play a vital role in the delivery, financing and evaluation of mental health services.

title: National Health Information Center
content: Puts health professionals and consumers who have health questions in touch with those organizations that are best able to provide answers.  Includes links to toll-free numbers, national health days and clearinghouses on health-related issues.

title: National Hospice & Palliative Care Organization (NHPCO)
content: Find palliative care programs and professionals in the United States. Provides a list of End-of-Life Care Resources.

title: Nurses Organization of Veterans Affairs Foundation (NOVA)
content: Supports the advancement of VA nursing through building awareness of the need to recruit, retain and continuously train qualified VA nurses.

title: United Spinal Association
content: Join a national organization formed by paralyzed Veterans whose mission is to improve the quality of life of Americans with spinal cord injuries and disorders (SCI/D). Membership is free and open to all individuals with SCI/D.

title: National Rural Health Resource Center
content: Find information about innovations in providing care to rural areas. Connect with professional resources and other health care professionals.

title: The New York Academy of Traumatic Brain Injury
content: Organization dedicated to bring together TBI experts and educate the public.

title: TRICARE Manuals
content: Access to several TRICARE manuals that cover operations and TRICARE policy, including manuals on provider reimbursements.

title: TRICARE Reimbursement Rates
content: Learn about TRICARE reimbursement rates for inpatient services, outpatient services, Ambulatory Surgical Centers rates, and more.

title: TRICARE - Handbooks
content: Find resources available to answer questions about TRICARE programs, policies and procedures, or if you need assistance coordinating care for a TRICARE beneficiary. Additional Online TRICARE Manuals are also available.

title: TRICARE - Management Portal
content: Provides organization, operations and policy information for the TRICARE Management Activity staff, including the portal to the TRICARE University and the TRICARE Press Room.

title: TRICARE - Reimbursement Rates for Mental Health Benefits
content: Learn how TRICARE has increased mental health reimbursement rates by 5 percent for 24 mental health services and find the reimbursement rates for all procedures by locality.

title: Improving Patient Safety with the Military Electronic Health Record
content: Discusses improvement to patient safety with the DoD "one patient, one record" system.
